        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 1:51AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 151 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of West Odessa, or 13 miles southwest of Odessa, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Odessa, Midland International Air and Space Port, West Odessa,
Warfield, and Pleasant Farms.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 102 and 130.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
